website deltacom delta air lines inc delta nyse dal is a major american airline with its headquarters and largest hub at hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport in atlanta georgia the airline along with its subsidiaries and regional affiliates operate over  flights daily and serve an extensive domestic and international network that includes  destinations in  countries on six continents as of october  delta is one of the four founding members of the skyteam airline alliance and operates joint ventures with air franceklm alitalia korean air china eastern airlines virgin atlantic and virgin australia regional service is operated under the brand name delta connection one of the five remaining legacy carriers delta is the sixtholdest operating airline by foundation date and the oldest airline still operating in the united states the companys history can be traced back to huff daland dusters founded in  in macon georgia as a crop dusting operation the company moved to monroe louisiana and was later renamed delta air services in reference to the nearby mississippi delta region and commenced passenger services on june   among predecessors of todays delta air lines western airlines and northwest airlines began flying passengers in  and  respectively in  delta air lines was the worlds largest airline in terms of scheduled passengers carried  million and the secondlargest in terms of both revenue passengerkilometers flown  billion and capacity  billion asmweek march  contents  history  predecessors  defunct delta subsidiaries  operations  headquarters and offices  branding  hubs  current hubs  former hubs  personnel  employee relations  destinations  alliances and codeshare agreements  air france–klm and alitalia joint venture  joint venture with virgin atlantic  fleet  cabin  delta one  premium select  first class  delta comfort  main cabin  basic economy  onboard amenities  wifi  inflight entertainment  history  current fleet  delta sky magazine  reward programs  skymiles  sky clubs  skybonus  environmental initiatives  sponsorships  in popular culture  deltalina  accidents and incidents  hijackings  see also  references  external links historyedit main article history of delta air lines restored huffdaland duster delta douglas dc circa  delta boeing  at london in  a delta air lines er landing at new york jfk airport delta air lines began as a crop dusting operation called huff daland dusters incorporated the company was founded on may   in macon georgia and moved to monroe louisiana in  they flew a huffdaland duster the first true crop duster designed to combat the boll weevil infestation of cotton crops collett e woolman one of the original directors purchased the company on september   and renamed it delta air service service began on june   with the inaugural flight between dallas texas and jackson mississippi delta moved its headquarters to its current location in atlanta in  and continued to grow through the addition of routes and the acquisition of other airlines they replaced propeller planes with jets in the s and entered international competition to europe in the s and across the pacific in the s deltas more recent history is marked by its emergence from bankruptcy on april   and the subsequent merger with northwest airlines the merger was announced april   and was set to create the worlds largest airline after approval of the merger on october   northwest continued to operate as a wholly owned subsidiary of delta until december   when both carriers operating certificates were merged the delta certificate was kept delta completed the integration with northwest on january   when their reservation systems and websites were combined and the northwest airlines name and brand were officially retired predecessorsedit a northwest airlines airbus a shortly before the merger with delta in  delta air lines as it exists today is the result of numerous mergers over its history predecessor carriers forming the current delta air lines include chicago and southern air lines formed in  merged into delta in  delta flew under the carrier name of deltacs for the following two years northeast airlines formed in  merged into delta in august  northwest airlines formed in  merged into delta in  also known as northwest orient airlines from  republic airlines formed in  merged into northwest airlines in  hughes airwest formed in  as air west as a result of a three way merger of bonanza air lines pacific air lines and west coast airlines name change to hughes airwest in  merged into republic airlines in  bonanza air lines formed in  merged into air westhughes airwest in  pacific air lines formed in  merged into air westhughes airwest in  west coast airlines formed in  merged into air westhughes airwest in  north central airlines formed in  as wisconsin central airlines name change to north central airlines in  merged into republic airlines in  southern airways formed in  merged into republic airlines in  pan american world airways formed in  upon its bankruptcy in  delta bought a selection of pan ams assets and routes and merged them into its operations atlantic gulf and caribbean airways formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  american overseas airlines formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  aviation corporation of the americasamerican international airways formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  national airlines formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  western airlines formed in  merged into delta in  standard air lines formed in  merged into western airlines in  defunct delta subsidiariesedit delta express boeing  in  comair began services in march  and was headquartered at cincinnatinorthern kentucky international airport after successfully introducing seat planes into the united states it was acquired by delta in october  comair became the main carrier of delta connection and operated over  daily flights from cincinnatinorthern kentucky international airport throughout the us mexico and caribbean comair ceased operations on september   and was folded into delta connection operations delta express began service in october  in an attempt by delta to compete with low cost airlines on leisureoriented routes its main base of operations was orlando international airport and it used boeing – aircraft it ceased operations in november  after song was established song began service on april   as a singleclass airline operated by delta to compete directly with jetblue airways from both airlines hub at new york–jfk while the brand was considered a successful addition to the northeasttoflorida market financially the airline suffered on may   song was folded into the delta mainline brand song used boeing  aircraft operationsedit delta air lines headquarters in atlanta headquarters and officesedit deltas corporate headquarters is located on a corporate campus on the northern boundary of hartsfieldjackson atlanta international airport within the city limits of atlanta this location has served as deltas headquarters since  when the company relocated its corporate offices from monroe louisiana to greater atlanta the crop dusting division of delta remained headquartered in monroe until delta ceased crop dusting in  prior to  the delta corporate campus an acre  ha plot of land in proximity to the old hartsfield airport terminal was outside the city of atlanta limits in unincorporated fulton county on august   the atlanta city council approved the annexation of  acres  ha of land an area containing the delta headquarters as of  delta would have had to begin paying  annually to the city of atlanta in taxes in september  the airline sued the city challenging the annexation on the basis of the constitutionality of the  city of atlanta annexation of the hartsfield old terminal the city of atlanta was only permitted to annex areas that are adjacent to areas already in the atlanta city limits in addition to hosting deltas corporate headquarters hartsfieldjackson is also the home of delta techops the airlines primary maintenance repair and overhaul arm and the largest fullservice airline mro in north america specializing in engines components airframe and line maintenance delta maintains a large presence in the twin cities with over  employees in the region as well as significant corporate support functions housed in the minneapolis area including the companys information technology divisional offices an airbus a painted in deltas current livery upward  onward brandingedit deltas logo often called the widget was originally unveiled in  its triangle shape is taken from the greek letter delta and recalls the airlines origins in the mississippi delta it is also said to be reminiscent of the sweptwing design of the dc deltas first jet aircraft deltas current livery is called upward  onward it features a white fuselage with the companys name in blue lettering and a widget on the vertical stabilizer delta introduced its current livery in  as part of a rebranding after it emerged from bankruptcy the new livery consists of four colors while the old one called colors in motion used eight this meant the switch saved the airline money by removing one day from each aircrafts painting cycle the airline took four years to repaint all of its aircraft into the current scheme including aircraft inherited from northwest airlines hubsedit current hubsedit the fly delta air lines marker at hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport emphasizes the presence of the airline delta has ten domestic hubs and four international hubs delta carries more passengers than any other airline at atlanta cincinnati detroit minneapolisst paul new yorkjfk new yorklaguardia and salt lake city amsterdam airport schiphol – one of the three european hubs operated in conjunction with skyteam and joint venture partner klm delta inherited its alliance with klm in the merger with northwest airlines charles de gaulle airport paris – deltas second european hub operated in conjunction with skyteam partner air france cincinnatinorthern kentucky international airport – prior to the merger with northwest airlines cincinnati was the second largest hub for delta with  daily departures since the merger service has been drastically cut mainly due to its proximity to the detroit hub as well as the shutdown of comair service levels have since stabilized and seat capacity has been increasing since late  detroit metropolitan airport – acquired through the merger with northwest detroit is deltas secondlargest hub by daily flights and third largest by seats available it serves as the airlines primary asian gateway for the northeastern united states hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport – in addition to its corporate headquarters delta also operates delta techops deltas primary maintenance base and the largest airline hub in the world in atlanta it is also deltas main gateway to latin america and the caribbean and a secondary transatlantic gateway heathrow airport london lhr – deltas third european hub operated in conjunction with codeshare partner virgin atlantic with whom delta also owns a  stake john f kennedy international airport new york city – a major international gateway especially to europe also offers service on many transcontinental prestige routes to west coast destinations including los angeles and san francisco laguardia airport new york city – an important domestic hub created as a result of a slot swap with us airways delta service at laguardia covers numerous east coast us cities and a number of regional destinations in the us and canada logan international airport boston – a hub for delta in the second half of the th century through the early s in  terminal a was built for deltas sole use however when delta went bankrupt they leased  of the  gates in the terminal today delta still has a large share in the boston market with daily international flights to various cities in central america canada and major european cities they now occupy  of the  gates and have recently opened a second sky club los angeles international airport – delta inherited its lax hub from western airlines but dismantled it in the mids opting to relocate most of those aircraft to the us east coast since then it has reopened the hub offering service to latin america asia and australia as well as major domestic bases and west coast regional destinations as of may  delta captured a  passenger market share with  daily departures minneapolis–saint paul international airport – once the headquarters for northwest airlines minneapolis is deltas third largest hub by daily flights and second by seats available delta served  passengers at msp in  and accounts for more than  of the airports traffic service includes a number of regional destinations and most major canadian and american metropolitan areas as well as select destinations in latin america europe and asia narita international airport tokyo – deltas intraasia hub inherited from northwest service allows connections from several of deltas domestic hubs to other destinations in asia including singapore shanghai and manila several narita routes have been cut recently including new york jfk bangkok and osaka this trend along with the growth of transpacific flights to asia from the growing seattle hub has led to speculation that delta might be downsizing or closing the narita hub salt lake city international airport – deltas fifthlargest hub inherited during the  western airlines merger service from salt lake city covers most major us destinations as well as a number of regional destinations in the us and canada and select cities in europe and hawaii seattle–tacoma international airport – delta announced seattles hub status in  the hub serves as an important gateway to asia delta started aggressively building its presence in seattle in  sparking tension with seattlebased alaska airlines delta continues to grow in seattle adding more regional and domestic service as well as new asian destinations these statistics are current as of february  ranked by daily departures rank airport daily departures destinations served  atlanta atl    detroit dtw    minneapolisst paul msp    new york city lga    salt lake city slc    new york city jfk    los angeles lax    seattletacoma sea    cincinnati cvg    boston bos    amsterdam ams    tokyo nrt    paris cdg    london lhr   former hubsedit ohare international airport chicago – delta operated a small hub at ohare until the early s dallasfort worth international airport – delta at one time operated over  flights per day from dfw making it their thirdlargest hub at the time delta closed the hub in february  due to competition with american airlines which has their main hub there frankfurt airport – upon pan ams bankruptcy delta acquired its frankfurt hub and the remainder of its atlantic division delta closed the hub in  memphis international airport – delta inherited the memphis hub operation in the northwest merger after several rounds of cuts hub status was removed in  orlando international airport – delta built up its orlando hub alongside comair starting in  going on to become the official airline of walt disney world the airport later became the hub for delta express and song before delta pulled back mainline presence in the mid s portland international airport – delta built up its portland hub in the late s to gain a presence in the us to asia market the hub operated most of deltas flights to asia but was slowly reduced due to the japanese and korean economic recession and closed in  personneledit between its mainline operation and subsidiaries and as of march  delta employs nearly  people joanne smith is executive vice president and chief human resources officer responsible for the oversight and support of personnel needs at delta she was appointed on october   replacing mike campbell employee relationsedit deltas  mainline pilots are represented by the air line pilots association international and are the unions largest pilot group the companys approximately  flight dispatchers are represented by the professional airline flight control association pafcacitation needed not counting the pilots and flight dispatchers delta is the only one of the five largest airlines in the united states and one of only two in the top  the other being jetblue whose nonpilot usa domestic staff is entirely nonunion the nonpilot nonunionization caused issues during and after the merger with northwest whose employees had a much higher rate of unionization while pilots at both airlines were unionized it was necessary to hold unionization votes for all other groups of employees northwest airlines flight attendants were formerly represented by the association of flight attendants afa a vote on unionization with the afa at the postmerger delta was held on  november  unionization was narrowly rejected by flight attendants with  votes against unionization and  in favor the afa accused delta of interference in the vote and requested the national mediation board nmb investigate and order a second vote the nmb investigation found that the election was not compromised and dismissed the claim currently both the international association of machinists and aerospace workers and a coalition of the afa and the transport workers union of america are seeking to hold unionization votes for delta flight attendants destinationsedit further information delta air lines destinations and delta connection destinations delta air lines destinations as of march  yearround destinations are red seasonal destinations are pink and former destinations are dark grey as of march  delta operates more than  flights per day delta connection operates  daily flights it is one of the few airlines to fly to all six inhabited continents along with air canada air china air france british airways emirates etihad airways korean air qantas qatar airways singapore airlines and south african airways delta is the only us carrier that is flying to accra copenhagen dakar dusseldorf johannesburg lagos moscow nice prague reykjavik and stuttgart it is also the only us carrier that has scheduled service to africa alliances and codeshare agreementsedit delta was a founding member of the skyteam alliance in  in addition to skyteam partners delta air lines also has codeshare agreements with the following airlines aeroflot aerolíneas argentinas aeroméxico air europa air france alitalia china airlines china eastern airlines china southern airlines czech airlines gol transportes aéreos hawaiian airlines jet airways klm korean air seaborne airlines transavia virgin atlantic virgin australia westjet air france–klm and alitalia joint ventureedit inherited from the northwestklm relationship which is older than any of the three major airline alliances including skyteam itself delta has a transatlantic joint venture with air franceklm and alitalia the program coordinates transatlantic operations including ticket pricing schedules capacity and revenue on january   the european commission launched an investigation into the impact of the joint venture on competition on the routes that it covers joint venture with virgin atlanticedit on december   delta announced that it would spend  million to acquire a  percent stake in virgin atlantic these shares were previously held by singapore airlines as a part of this agreement both airlines would share the costs and revenues from all of the joint venture flights the airlines operated the two airlines planned to operate a total of  roundtrip flights between the uk and north america including nine daily roundtrip flights between london heathrow and new york city airports john f kennedy international airport and newark liberty international airport the two airlines application for antitrust immunity was granted by the united states department of transportation on september   fleetedit delta air lines has the largest boeing  fleet of any airline main article delta air lines fleet as of january update delta operates a fleet of more than  aircraft manufactured by airbus boeing and mcdonnell douglas delta operates the largest boeing  boeing  boeing  mcdonnell douglas md and mcdonnell douglas md fleets in the world and the largest airbus a fleet of any us airline prior to its  merger with northwest airlines deltas fleet was made up of solely boeing and mcdonnell douglas aircraft airbus aircraft from northwest joined the fleet after the merger and more have since been added unlike other us legacy carriers delta often seeks to acquire and utilize older aircraft especially narrowbodies and they have created an extensive mro maintenance repair and overhaul organization called techops to support them the oldest aircraft in the fleet are the mcdonnell douglas mds with an average age of over  years however in early  delta began talks with airbus boeing and bombardier to discuss replacing the mcdonnell douglas dcs mds and older a and  aircraft on august   delta placed an order for  boeing er aircraft and deferred an order of  small narrowbody jets until  as part of its strategy to utilize less expensive used airplanes delta agreed in  to lease  boeing s acquired by southwest airlines during their acquisition of airtran airways they would be used as replacements for the dc fleet and some seat regional aircraft like the crj and  the first revenue flight was on october   delta officially retired its last dc on january   it was used on an asneeded basis until january   when the last one was removed from service delta was the final us carrier operating the dc as a continuation of the narrowbody fleet refresh and expansion delta ordered  bombardier cs aircraft and an additional  options on april   becoming the first american carrier to order the type the airline has not been as keen to acquire or operate aging widebody aircraft on august   delta announced they would begin to retire the aging boeing  fleet acquired as part of the northwest merger during a  earnings call ceo richard anderson announced that they would be retired by the end of  on november   the airline announced an order for  airbus a and  airbus a aircraft to replace the  fleet as it was retired as well as some aging s a deliveries will begin in the second quarter of  while the first a is scheduled for  cabinedit delta underwent a cabin branding upgrade in  the airline now offers or plans to offer  different cabin service options delta one delta premium select first class comfort main cabin and basic economy availability and exact details vary by route and aircraft type delta oneedit delta one cabin on a boeing  then known as businesselite delta one is the airlines premier business class product being available on long haul international flights as well as transcontinental service from new yorkjfk to los angeles and san francisco delta one features lieflat seating on all aircraft types and direct aisle access from every seat on all types except the boeing  the boeing er and boeing er seats designed by james thompson feature a spacesaving design whereby the seats are staggered such that when in the fully flat position the foot of each bed extends under the armrests of the seat in front of it delta one cabins on the boeing erlr fleet are configured in a herringbone layout while all boeing  and airbus a cabins featuring the cirrus flatbed sleeper suite by zodiac seats us are configured in a reverse herringbone pattern all seats are also equipped with a personal on demand inflightentertainment ife system universal powerports a movable reading light and a folding work table passengers also receive complimentary chef curated meals refreshments alcoholic beverages an amenity kit premium bedding and preflight sky club access in august  delta announced the introduction of delta one suites on select widebody fleets the suites will feature a door to the aisle for enhanced privacy as well as improved storage space a larger ife screen and updated design the suites will roll out on the airbus a fleet slated to begin delivery in fall  followed by the boeing  premium selectedit in april  ceo ed bastian announced that a new premium economy cabin will be added since renamed to premium select this cabin will feature extra legroom adjustable leg rests extra seat pitch width and recline and a new premium service delta will introduce it on its new airbus a slated for delivery in fall  followed by the boeing  first classedit first class is offered on mainline domestic flights except those featuring delta one service select short and mediumhaul international flights and delta connection aircraft with more than  seats seats range from  to  inches  to  cm wide and have between  and  inches  and  cm of pitch passengers in this class receive a wider variety of free snacks compared to main cabin as well as free drinks and alcohol and full meal service on flights  miles and longer certain aircraft also feature powerports at each seat and free entertainment products from delta studio first class passengers are also eligible for priority boarding delta comfortedit delta comfort seats are installed on all aircraft and feature – inches – mm of pitch on all delta one configured aircraft – inches – mm of pitch and  percent more recline over standard main cabin seats additional amenities include sky priority boarding dedicated overhead space complimentary beer wine and spirits on flight  miles or more and complimentary premium snacks on flights  miles or more complimentary premium entertainment is available via delta studio with free headsets available on most flights on transcontinental flights between jfklaxsfo delta comfort passengers also get luvo snack wraps medallion members can upgrade from main cabin to comfort for free while other customers can upgrade for a fee or with skymiles main cabinedit main cabin on a boeing – main cabin also known as economy class is available on all aircraft with seats ranging from  to  inches  to  cm wide and  to  inches  to  cm of pitch the main cabin on boeing    and selected boeing   and mcdonnell douglas md aircraft have an articulating seat bottom where the seat bottom moves forward in addition to the seat back tilting backwards when recliningcitation needed main cabin passengers receive complimentary snacks and nonalcoholic drinks on all flights  miles  km or longer alcoholic beverages are also available for purchase complimentary meals and alcoholic drinks are provided on longhaul international flights as well as selected transcontinental domestic flights such as between new york–jfk and seattle san francisco los angeles and san diego as part of deltas flight fuel buy on board program meals are available for purchase on other north american flights  miles  km or longer delta operated a different buy on board program between  and  the previous program had items from differing providers depending on the origin and destination of the flight prices ranged up to   when adjusted for inflation the airline started the service on a few selected flights in july  and the meal service was initially offered on  flights delta ended this buy on board program in  instead delta began offering snacks at no extra charge on flights over  minutes to most us domestic flights and some flights to the caribbean and latin america beginning in midmarch  the airline planned to stop providing pillows on flights within the  contiguous us states bermuda canada the caribbean and central america in addition the airline increased the price of alcoholic beverages on delta mainline flights from   when adjusted for inflation to   when adjusted for inflation the increase in alcohol prices did not occur on song flights basic economyedit basic economy is a basic version of main cabin offering the same services with fewer flexibility options for a lower price examples of fewer flexibility options include no ticket changes no paid or complimentary upgrades regardless of frequentflier status and only having a seat assigned at checkin onboard amenitiesedit wifiedit on august   delta announced it would be installing the aircell mobile broadband network gogo which enables customers traveling with wifi enabled devices such as laptops smartphones and tablets to access the internet for a fee gogo was initially offered on deltas fleet of mcdonnell douglas md and md aircraft but has expanded to the remaining domestic fleet as well as delta connection aircraft with a first class cabin delta has the largest fleet of wifiequipped aircraft in the world the airline introduced its first inflight wifi on international routes to tokyo from los angeles and atlanta in march  and stated its intent to offer the service on all transoceanic flight routes by the end of  even though delta has announced the retirement of its  fleet all delta s are wifiequipped and delta is currently installing wifi on the  fleet inflight entertainmentedit historyedit in the s audio programming was introduced where passengers wore headphones consisting of hollow tubes piping in music these were installed in some delta aircraft some early widebodied aircraft including the lockheed l boeing  and  fleet had movies projected on to the cabin bulkhead also during the late s and early s crt monitors over the aisles were added to the  fleet making them the first narrowbody aircraft to feature video entertainment the md introduced deltas first ife system with lcd monitors in  and the  introduced deltas first inseat video system in  initially using the rockwell collins total entertainment system deltas first alldigital ife system with avod panasonic efx was first introduced in  on deltas former lowcost subsidiary song the rockwell collins ife system on the s was replaced by the panasonic efx system in  followed by the panasonic ex in  the panasonic efx and ex systems are trademarked by delta as delta on demand in the spring of  delta installed the panasonic efx avod system in economy on six ers that are used on routes that are  hours or longer delta also announced it would be installing avod in economy class on all boeing er and  aircraft over the next  years on july   delta announced that it would be the launch customer of the new ex avod system with the eco i integrated smart monitor a new ultralightweight ife system by panasonic avionics corporation and zodiac seats us the systems have been installed on the entire  fleet as of october  and are currently being installed on the er fleet except for the six aircraft previously retrofitted with the efx system in  a different version of the integrated smart monitor developed by panasonic avionics corporation and be aerospace is currently being installed on the airbus a fleet these seats will also be installed on the boeing  and new boeing er fleet and will replace the existing seats and monitors on the international boeing  fleet in  delta began replacing the overhead crt monitors on the premerger delta  fleet with new lcd monitors this was completed in late  the er fleet initially featured lcds over the aisles but were replaced in  by the panasonic efx avod system when the last of the ers were converted from domestic to international use crt projectors were originally featured in economy class on boeing –s with the international ers also featuring ceilingmounted crt displays over the aisles which have since replaced by lcd monitors and are now in the process of being converted to the efx avod system when deltas extwa etops s were first delivered they featured a system made by sony transcom a former subsidiary of sony now sold to rockwell collins system that was factory installed for twa the system featured overhead dropdown lcd monitors similar to deltas nontranscon s and s delta replaced the sony transcom system with the panasonic efx system featuring inseat video and avod at the same time as the new businesselite seats and slimline economy class seats were installed current fleetedit audio and video are available on all aircraft except for the airbus a mcdonnell douglas md and md selected boeing  and delta connection aircraft boeing er lr and  aircraft along with those  and a aircraft that have completed cabin modifications feature the panasonic ex system compared to the older efx system this offers greater storage capacity as well as lighter and larger personal video screens boeing er aircraft selected  aircraft as well as the remaining internationally configured boeing er aircraft that have not completed cabin modifications use the panasonic efx avod system on these  aircraft avod is available only in the delta one class while the system includes overhead lcd monitors and audio programming for passengers seated in the economy cabin the unmodified airbus a aircraft feature the panasonic i avod system in all cabins this system includes supplemental lcd monitors over the aisles for displaying the safety video and moving map domestic boeing –s boeing –s as well as selected transcontinental boeing –s and selected boeing –s using the panasonic efx system also feature live television via dish network in both first class and economy some boeing s as well as all boeing –s feature systems with dropdown lcd displays below the overhead bins all aircraft with avod feature panasonics ixplor moving map program s with overhead video and the coach sections of er aircraft with overhead video feature the rockwell collins airshow moving map which is often shown during takeoff and landing other aircraft formerly equipped with the rockwell collins airshow moving map included the lockheed l and  mcdonnell douglas md and boeing er and er the l and md fleet have since been retired while the er and er have since had their airshow systems replaced by the panasonic ixplor system built into the efx and ex avod systems delta sky magazineedit delta sky magazine and its online edition are published by msp communications in minneapolis minnesota reward programsedit skymilesedit main article skymiles skymiles is the frequent flyer program for delta air lines sky clubsedit delta air lines airport lounges are called sky clubs membership options include single visit passes and annual memberships that can be purchased with either money or miles international business class passengers get free access membership can also be granted through top level delta status or with the purchase of some american express credit cards features vary by location but generally include free drinks including alcoholic beverages snacks and reading material wifi is free for members and guests and is mostly provided in the usa by att other benefits for sky club members include reciprocal lounge access with other skyteam members and deltas other partners originally deltas membershipbased airport clubs were called crown room lounges with northwests called worldclubs skybonusedit on november   delta air lines launched skybonusnot in citation given a program aimed toward smalltomedium businesses spending between  and  annually on air travel businesses can earn points toward free travel and upgrades as well as sky club memberships and skymiles silver medallion status points are earned on paid travel based on a variety of fare amount paid booking code and place origin or destination while enrolled businesses are able to earn points toward free travel the travelling passenger is still eligible to earn skymiles during his or her travel in early  delta air lines merged its skybonus program with northwests similar biz perks program environmental initiativesedit in  delta air lines was given an award from the united states environmental protection agencys design for the environment dfe program for their use of prekote a more environmentally friendly nonhexavalent chromium surface pretreatment on its aircraft replacing hazardous chemicals formerly used to improve paint adhesion and prevent corrosion in addition prekote reduces water usage by twothirds and reduces wastewater treatment prekote is also saving money by reducing the time needed to paint each airplane with time savings of eight to ten percent it will save an estimated more than  million annually sponsorshipsedit boeing er painted in pink livery for breast cancer research foundation bcrf at munich airport in  delta served as the official airline of the  summer olympics in atlanta the  winter olympics held in salt lake city and is also the official airline for major league baseball teams such as the atlanta braves cincinnati reds detroit tigers minnesota twins new york mets new york yankees san diego padres st louis cardinals and the washington nationals delta also carries the buffalo sabres los angeles kings los angeles lakers los angeles sparks chelsea fc madison square garden seattle seahawks seattle sounders fc copa américa centenario atlanta dream atlanta falcons atlanta hawks atlanta united fc and the cleveland cavaliers delta awards the annual delta prize for global understanding in conjunction with the university of georgia vivint smart home arena in salt lake city home of the nbas utah jazz was originally known as the delta center delta held the naming rights to the arena from  to  and continues to be an official sponsor of the team delta was a sponsor of the  north american international auto show in detroit delta is the official airline for the grammy awards also in  delta is the official airline for the durham bulls minor league baseball team in august  delta continued its push into new york city by securing its first arts sponsorship the deal with the whitney museum makes delta the official and exclusive airline of the museum delta has sponsored various lgbt pride events in atlanta new york city salt lake city and detroit delta also sponsors the university of georgia and georgia tech athletics and provides transportation for away games delta air lines is the official airline of syracuse university athletics and has marketing relationships with eight additional ncaa athletic programs—boston college brigham young duke georgia tech university of georgia university of michigan university of minnesota and university of north carolina delta serves as the charter carrier for  ncaa football programs in  delta sponsored yomiuri giants a nippon professional baseball team this is the first time that delta sponsored a foreign sports team in popular cultureedit deltalinaedit main article deltalina as part of the rebranding project a safety video featuring a flight attendant showed up on youtube in early  getting over  million views and the attention of news outlets specifically for the videos tone mixed with the serious safety message the flight attendant katherine lee was dubbed deltalina by a member of flyertalk for her resemblance to angelina jolie delta had considered several styles for its current safety video including animation before opting for a video presenting a flight attendant speaking to the audience the video was filmed on a boeing  accidents and incidentsedit the following are major accidents and incidents that occurred on delta mainline aircraft for northwest airlines incidents see northwest airlines accidents and incidents for delta connection incidents see delta connection incidents and accidents delta air lines reported incidents flight date aircraft location description casualties fatal serious minor uninjured ground na april   dc columbus georgia a vultee bt owned by the tuskegee aviation institute landed on top of a dc which was flying from macon to columbus       march   dc chicago midway airport crashed near chicago municipal midway airport shortly after takeoff while en route to miami officials determined that longitudinal control of the airplane was lost resulting in the crash the cause for the loss of control remains undetermined       may   dc marshall texas crashed  miles  km east of marshall texas the flight which originated from dallas love field was on approach to shreveport louisiana the crash was attributed to adverse weather conditions with a thunderstorm in the area       may   convair  hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport crashed during a training exercise in atlanta the aircraft stalled and crashed killing all four crew members       march   dc louis armstrong new orleans international airport crashed during a training exercise near new orleans international airport the improper use of flight and power controls by both instructor and the captaintrainee during a simulated twoengine out landing approach resulted in the loss of control the aircraft crashed into a residential area destroying several homes and a motel complex and killing  people on the ground       may   dc greater southwest international airport crashed during landing procedures in fort worth texas the probable cause of the accident was wake turbulence resulting from a touchandgo landing moments before of american airlines flight  operated using a dc the right wing hit the ground causing a fire resulting in the aircraft being written off       december   convair  ohare international airport the delta cv taxied across runway l in heavy fog at the same time north central airlines flight  a dc took off from the same runway the aircraft collided    severity unknown    july   dc boston logan international airport crashed into a seawall contributing to the accident was a defective flight deck instrument giving the crew misleading guidance during the instrument approach in visibility less than a half mile with foot  m cloud ceilings  occupants died including leopold chouinard who died from burns months after the accident leaving no survivors       november   dc chattanooga metropolitan airport crashed into approach lights during a thunderstorm       august   lockheed l dallas–fort worth international airport on a fort lauderdale–dallasfort worth los angeles route the plane crashed due to severe microburstinduced wind shear one person on the ground was killed as the plane crossed a highway the crash would later become the subject of a television movie numerous changes to pilot wind shear training weather forecasting and wind shear detection were made as a result of this crash       july   lockheed l north atlantic ocean near collision with a continental  carrying  passengers and crew both the delta londoncincinnati and continental londonnewark were heading to the us with nearly  people total on both aircraft the delta flight strayed  miles  km off course to the south from its assigned c track during its flight and came within  feet  m of colliding with the  as the l flew under it in canadian airspace flying on the d track there are five westbound and five eastbound tracks from the united states to the united kingdom had the planes actually collided it could have tied the tenerife airport disaster as the deadliest aviation accident in history    all   august   boeing  dallas–fort worth international airport crashed after takeoff bound for salt lake city utah the investigation stated the probable cause of this accident to be improper configuration of the flaps and leading edge slats       july   md pensacola international airport an uncontained engine failure of the port left engine on the aircraft resulted in a fan hub piercing the cabin the flight was scheduled to fly to atlanta the aircraft involved in this accident nda was repaired as of february  the faa reports the aircraft involved in the incident is still in service        september   boeing – en route from boston logan international airport flight  bound for los angeles international airport was caught in the path of united airlines flight  the two aircraft were so close that atc were initially confused as to which plane had been hijacked the delta pilot managed to avoid united  and the flight was later diverted to cleveland hopkins international airport    all    february   mcdonnell douglas md dublin airport flight  from atlanta skidded off the runway at dublin airport in high winds the port engine of md nde had severe damage    all   march   mcdonnell douglas md laguardia airport while landing in heavy snowfall flight  from atlanta departed the left side of runway while traveling approximately  miles per hour  kmh coming to rest nearly perpendicular to the runway with its nose on an embankment beside the waters of flushing bay the accident resulted in damage to the aircrafts left wing including a fuel leak nose landing gear well main electronics bay nose radomeweather radar and undercarriage damage forward of the front doors the aircrafts braking system and condition of the runway surface are being considered as possible causes of the incident       june   boeing  over chinese airspace flight  from detroit metropolitan wayne county airport to seoul incheon international airport was over chinese airspace when the aircraft flew through a severe hailstorm this resulted in substantial damage to the aircrafts radome hail penetrating nose causing a large hole as well as leading edges of the wing destroyed and damage to the tail plane this aircraft was written off due to its age and because delta had already began retiring its boeing  fleet temporary repairs were made to make it airworthy and the aircraft was ferried from seoul to pinal airpark in marana arizona    all   august   airbus a en route from boston logan airport to salt lake city the plane had to make an emergency landing at the denver international airport after a hailstorm at the nebraskacolorado border about  nm east of denver severely damaged its windshields and nose cone impairing visibility through the windshields and disabling the weather radar engines were also damaged and the hail also partially tore the planes fuselage        july   boeing  over canadian airspace flight  from seattle to beijing had an altercation midflight where a male passenger named joseph daniel hudek attempted to open an emergency exit which is impossible at that altitude due to the difference in air pressure and assaulted a flight attendant in the firstclass cabin several other passengers became involved in the situation in an attempt to subdue hudek the flight returned to seattle without further incident where hudek was arrested the flight attendant and one other passenger who tried to subdue the suspect were taken to the hospital for nonlifethreatening injuries federal charges were filed against hudek and he may face up to  years in prison and fines up to us      the attempted bombing of northwest airlines flight  on december   occurred four days before the operating certificates of northwest and delta were combined december   the aircraft involved in the incident was in delta livery and reported in some early news reports as delta flight  hijackingsedit there have been over a dozen attempted hijackings that resulted in no injuries and the surrender of the often lone hijacker these incidents are not included the following are notable hijackings because of fatalities or success in forcing the aircraft to fly to another country in  a delta dc was hijacked to havana cuba this was the first successful hijacking to cuba from the us since citation needed and was the start of multiple hijacking attempts to cuba in the late s this coincided with the introduction of passenger screening using metal detectors in us airports starting in the late s additional hijackings that resulted in no injuries and the flight landing in cuba include march   delta  new orleansdallas  august   delta  miamitampa  july   delta  miamitampa  june   delta  new york laguardiafort lauderdale l july   a delta flight  a detroit to miami dc flight was hijacked to algiers algeria by  hijackers the aircraft stopped in boston to pick up an international navigator the flight was allowed to return with passengers to the us stopping in barcelona for refueling on february   samuel byck an unemployed tire salesman from pennsylvania stormed aboard delta air lines flight  dc flight at baltimore friendship airport now baltimorewashington international thurgood marshall airport scheduled to fly to atlanta and shot both pilots killing the first officer fred jones he intended to crash the plane into the white house after shooting the pilots the hijacker grabbed a passenger and demanded that she fly the aircraft the hijacking attempt ended when after a standoff with police byck was shot twice through an aircraft porthole by a md policeman severely wounding him before police stormed the plane byck killed himself the plane never left the gate during this incident on august   a delta air lines l on a san juan to los angeles flight was hijacked and flown to cuba the hijacker was jailed by cuban authorities and all passengers were released unharmed on september   a delta air lines new orleans to atlanta flight was taken over by two hijackers and forced to fly to cuba the flight continued to atlanta after stopping in havana the hijackers were imprisoned by cuban authorities one hijacker was released and later sought us residency the suspect was later arrested by us authorities in  and sentenced to  years in prison the following year see alsoedit book delta air lines atlanta portal companies portal aviation portal air transportation in the united states delta flight museum list of airlines of the united states list of airports in the united states list of companies of the united states transportation in the united states referencesedit notes  history newsdeltacom delta air lines inc october  retrieved january    the huff daland dusters cropdusting operation which formed the roots for delta founded in macon ga passenger airline founded  monroe la   norwood tom wegg john  north american airlines handbook rd ed sandpoint idaho airways international p  isbn    airline certificate information – detail view avinfofaagov federal aviation administration september   certificate number dalaa   a b delta air lines hub station amsterdam deltacom march   retrieved april     a b c d global network retrieved 