e ed bastian ceo glen hauenstein president revenue us  billion  operating income us  billion  net income us  billion  total assets us  billion  total equity us  billion  employees   website deltacom delta air lines inc delta nyse dal is a major american airline with its headquarters and largest hub at hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport in atlanta georgia the airline along with its subsidiaries and regional affiliates operate over  flights daily and serve an extensive domestic and international network that includes  destinations in  countries on six continents as of october  delta is one of the four founding members of the skyteam airline alliance and operates joint ventures with air franceklm alitalia korean air china eastern airlines virgin atlantic and virgin australia regional service is operated under the brand name delta connection one of the five remaining legacy carriers delta is the sixtholdest operating airline by foundation date and the oldest airline still operating in the united states the companys history can be traced back to huff daland dusters founded in  in macon georgia as a crop dusting operation the company moved to monroe louisiana and was later renamed delta air services in reference to the nearby mississippi delta region and commenced passenger services on june   among predecessors of todays delta air lines western airlines and northwest airlines began flying passengers in  and  respectively in  delta air lines was the worlds largest airline in terms of scheduled passengers carried  million and the secondlargest in terms of both revenue passengerkilometers flown  billion and capacity  billion asmweek march  contents  history  predecessors  defunct delta subsidiaries  operations  headquarters and offices  branding  hubs  current hubs  former hubs  personnel  employee relations  destinations  alliances and codeshare agreements  air france–klm and alitalia joint venture  joint venture with virgin atlantic  fleet  cabin  delta one  premium select  first class  delta comfort  main cabin  basic economy  onboard amenities  wifi  inflight entertainment  history  current fleet  delta sky magazine  reward programs  skymiles  sky clubs  skybonus  environmental initiatives  sponsorships  in popular culture  deltalina  accidents and incidents  hijackings  see also  references  external links historyedit main article history of delta air lines restored huffdaland duster delta douglas dc circa  delta boeing  at london in  a delta air lines er landing at new york jfk airport delta air lines began as a crop dusting operation called huff daland dusters incorporated the company was founded on may   in macon georgia and moved to monroe louisiana in  they flew a huffdaland duster the first true crop duster designed to combat the boll weevil infestation of cotton crops collett e woolman one of the original directors purchased the company on september   and renamed it delta air service service began on june   with the inaugural flight between dallas texas and jackson mississippi delta moved its headquarters to its current location in atlanta in  and continued to grow through the addition of routes and the acquisition of other airlines they replaced propeller planes with jets in the s and entered international competition to europe in the s and across the pacific in the s deltas more recent history is marked by its emergence from bankruptcy on april   and the subsequent merger with northwest airlines the merger was announced april   and was set to create the worlds largest airline after approval of the merger on october   northwest continued to operate as a wholly owned subsidiary of delta until december   when both carriers operating certificates were merged the delta certificate was kept delta completed the integration with northwest on january   when their reservation systems and websites were combined and the northwest airlines name and brand were officially retired predecessorsedit a northwest airlines airbus a shortly before the merger with delta in  delta air lines as it exists today is the result of numerous mergers over its history predecessor carriers forming the current delta air lines include chicago and southern air lines formed in  merged into delta in  delta flew under the carrier name of deltacs for the following two years northeast airlines formed in  merged into delta in august  northwest airlines formed in  merged into delta in  also known as northwest orient airlines from  republic airlines formed in  merged into northwest airlines in  hughes airwest formed in  as air west as a result of a three way merger of bonanza air lines pacific air lines and west coast airlines name change to hughes airwest in  merged into republic airlines in  bonanza air lines formed in  merged into air westhughes airwest in  pacific air lines formed in  merged into air westhughes airwest in  west coast airlines formed in  merged into air westhughes airwest in  north central airlines formed in  as wisconsin central airlines name change to north central airlines in  merged into republic airlines in  southern airways formed in  merged into republic airlines in  pan american world airways formed in  upon its bankruptcy in  delta bought a selection of pan ams assets and routes and merged them into its operations atlantic gulf and caribbean airways formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  american overseas airlines formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  aviation corporation of the americasamerican international airways formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  national airlines formed in  merged into pan american world airways in  western airlines formed in  merged into delta in  standard air lines formed in  merged into western airlines in  defunct delta subsidiariesedit delta express boeing  in  comair began services in march  and was headquartered at cincinnatinorthern kentucky international airport after successfully introducing seat planes into the united states it was acquired by delta in october  comair became the main carrier of delta connection and operated over  daily flights from cincinnatinorthern kentucky international airport throughout the us mexico and caribbean comair ceased operations on september   and was folded into delta connection operations delta express began service in october  in an attempt by delta to compete with low cost airlines on leisureoriented routes its main base of operations was orlando international airport and it used boeing – aircraft it ceased operations in november  after song was established song began service on april   as a singleclass airline operated by delta to compete directly with jetblue airways from both airlines hub at new york–jfk while the brand was considered a successful addition to the northeasttoflorida market financially the airline suffered on may   song was folded into the delta mainline brand song used boeing  aircraft operationsedit delta air lines headquarters in atlanta headquarters and officesedit deltas corporate headquarters is located on a corporate campus on the northern boundary of hartsfieldjackson atlanta international airport within the city limits of atlanta this location has served as deltas headquarters since  when the company relocated its corporate offices from monroe louisiana to greater atlanta the crop dusting division of delta remained headquartered in monroe until delta ceased crop dusting in  prior to  the delta corporate campus an acre  ha plot of land in proximity to the old hartsfield airport terminal was outside the city of atlanta limits in unincorporated fulton county on august   the atlanta city council approved the annexation of  acres  ha of land an area containing the delta headquarters as of  delta would have had to begin paying  annually to the city of atlanta in taxes in september  the airline sued the city challenging the annexation on the basis of the constitutionality of the  city of atlanta annexation of the hartsfield old terminal the city of atlanta was only permitted to annex areas that are adjacent to areas already in the atlanta city limits in addition to hosting deltas corporate headquarters hartsfieldjackson is also the home of delta techops the airlines primary maintenance repair and overhaul arm and the largest fullservice airline mro in north america specializing in engines components airframe and line maintenance delta maintains a large presence in the twin cities with over  employees in the region as well as significant corporate support functions housed in the minneapolis area including the companys information technology divisional offices an airbus a painted in deltas current livery upward  onward brandingedit deltas logo often called the widget was originally unveiled in  its triangle shape is taken from the greek letter delta and recalls the airlines origins in the mississippi delta it is also said to be reminiscent of the sweptwing design of the dc deltas first jet aircraft deltas current livery is called upward  onward it features a white fuselage with the companys name in blue lettering and a widget on the vertical stabilizer delta introduced its current livery in  as part of a rebranding after it emerged from bankruptcy the new livery consists of four colors while the old one called colors in motion used eight this meant the switch saved the airline money by removing one day from each aircrafts painting cycle the airline took four years to repaint all of its aircraft into the current scheme including aircraft inherited from northwest airlines hubsedit current hubsedit the fly delta air lines marker at hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport emphasizes the presence of the airline delta has ten domestic hubs and four international hubs delta carries more passengers than any other airline at atlanta cincinnati detroit minneapolisst paul new yorkjfk new yorklaguardia and salt lake city amsterdam airport schiphol – one of the three european hubs operated in conjunction with skyteam and joint venture partner klm delta inherited its alliance with klm in the merger with northwest airlines charles de gaulle airport paris – deltas second european hub operated in conjunction with skyteam partner air france cincinnatinorthern kentucky international airport – prior to the merger with northwest airlines cincinnati was the second largest hub for delta with  daily departures since the merger service has been drastically cut mainly due to its proximity to the detroit hub as well as the shutdown of comair service levels have since stabilized and seat capacity has been increasing since late  detroit metropolitan airport – acquired through the merger with northwest detroit is deltas secondlargest hub by daily flights and third largest by seats available it serves as the airlines primary asian gateway for the northeastern united states hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport – in addition to its corporate headquarters delta also operates delta techops deltas primary maintenance base and the largest airline hub in the world in atlanta it is also deltas main gateway to latin america and the caribbean and a secondary transatlantic gateway heathrow airport london lhr – deltas third european hub operated in conjunction with codeshare partner virgin atlantic with whom delta also owns a  stake john f kennedy international airport new york city – a major international gateway especially to europe also offers service on many transcontinental prestige routes to west coast destinations including los angeles and san francisco laguardia airport new york city – an important domestic hub created as a result of a slot swap with us airways delta service at laguardia covers numerous east coast us cities and a number of regional destinations in the us and canada logan international airport boston – a hub for delta in the second half of the th century through the early s in  terminal a was built for deltas sole use however when delta went bankrupt they leased  of the  gates in the terminal today delta still has a large share in the boston market with daily international flights to various cities in central america canada and major european cities they now occupy  of the  gates and have recently opened a second sky club los angeles international airport – delta inherited its lax hub from western airlines but dismantled it in the mids opting to relocate most of those aircraft to the us east coast since then it has reopened the hub offering service to latin america asia and australia as well as major domestic bases and west coast regional destinations as of may  delta captured a  passenger market share with  daily departures minneapolis–saint paul international airport – once the headquarters for northwest airlines minneapolis is deltas third largest hub by daily flights and second by seats available delta served  passengers at msp in  and accounts for more than  of the airports traffic service includes a number of regional destinations and most major canadian and american metropolitan areas as well as select destinations in latin america europe and asia narita international airport tokyo – deltas intraasia hub inherited from northwest service allows connections from several of deltas domestic hubs to other destinations in asia including singapore shanghai and manila several narita routes have been cut recently including new york jfk bangkok and osaka this trend along with the growth of transpacific flights to asia from the growing seattle hub has led to speculation that delta might be downsizing or closing the narita hub salt lake city international airport – deltas fifthlargest hub inherited during the  western airlines merger service from salt lake city covers most major us destinations as well as a number of regional destinations in the us and canada and select cities in europe and hawaii seattle–tacoma international airport – delta announced seattles hub status in  the hub serves as an important gateway to asia delta started aggressively building its presence in seattle in  sparking tension with seattlebased alaska airlines delta continues to grow in seattle adding more regional and domestic service as well as new asian destinations these statistics are current as of february  ranked by daily departures rank airport daily departures destinations served  atlanta atl    detroit dtw    minneapolisst paul msp    new york city lga    salt lake city slc    new york city jfk    los angeles lax    seattletacoma sea    cincinnati cvg    boston bos    amsterdam ams    tokyo nrt    paris cdg    london lhr   former hubsedit ohare international airport chicago – delta operated a small hub at ohare until the early s dallasfort worth international airport – delta at one time operated over  flights per day from dfw making it their thirdlargest hub at the time delta closed the hub in february  due to competition with american airlines which has their main hub there frankfurt airport – upon pan ams bankruptcy delta acquired its frankfurt hub and the remainder of its atlantic division delta closed the hub in  memphis international airport – delta inherited the memphis hub operation in the northwest merger after several rounds of cuts hub status was removed in  orlando international airport – delta built up its orlando hub alongside comair starting in  going on to become the official airline of walt disney world the airport later became the hub for delta express and song before delta pulled back mainline presence in the mid s portland international airport – delta built up its portland hub in the late s to gain a presence in the us to asia market the hub operated most of deltas flights to asia but was slowly reduced due to the japanese and korean economic recession and closed in  personneledit between its mainline operation and subsidiaries and as of march  delta employs nearly  people joanne smith is executive vice president and chief human resources officer responsible for the oversight and support of personnel needs at delta she was appointed on october   replacing mike campbell employee relationsedit deltas  mainline pilots are represented by the air line pilots association international and are the unions largest pilot group the companys approximately  flight dispatchers are represented by the professional airline flight control association pafcacitation needed not counting the pilots and flight dispatchers delta is the only one of the five largest airlines in the united states and one of only two in the top  the other being jetblue whose nonpilot usa domestic staff is entirely nonunion the nonpilot nonunionization caused issues during and after the merger with northwest whose employees had a much higher rate of unionization while pilots at both airlines were unionized it was necessary to hold unionization votes for all other groups of employees northwest airlines flight attendants were formerly represented by the association of flight attendants afa a vote on unionization with the afa at the postmerger delta was held on  november  unionization was narrowly rejected by flight attendants with  votes against unionization and  in favor the afa accused delta of interference in the vote and requested the national mediation board nmb investigate and order a second vote the nmb investigation found that the election was not compromised and dismissed the claim currently both the international association of machinists and aerospace workers and a coalition of the afa and the transport workers union of america are seeking to hold unionization votes for delta flight attendants destinationsedit further information delta air lines destinations and delta connection destinations delta air lines destinations as of march  yearround destinations are red seasonal destinations are pink and former destinations are dark grey as of march  delta operates more than  flights per day delta connection operates  daily flights it is one of the few airlines to fly to all six inhabited continents along with air canada air china air france british airways emirates etihad airways korean air qantas qatar airways singapore airlines and south african airways delta is the only us carrier that is flying to accra copenhagen dakar dusseldorf johannesburg lagos moscow nice prague reykjavik and stuttgart it is also the only us carrier that has scheduled service to africa alliances and codeshare agreementsedit delta was a founding member of the skyteam alliance in  in addition to skyteam partners delta air lines also has codeshare agreements with the following airlines aeroflot aerolíneas argentinas aeroméxico air europa air france alitalia china airlines china eastern airlines china southern airlines czech airlines gol transportes aéreos hawaiian airlines jet airways klm korean air seaborne airlines transavia virgin atlantic virgin australia westjet air france–klm and alitalia joint ventureedit inherited from the northwestklm relationship which is older than any of the three major airline alliances including skyteam itself delta has a transatlantic joint venture with air franceklm and alitalia the program coordinates transatlantic operations including ticket pricing schedules capacity and revenue on january   the european commission launched an investigation into the impact of the joint venture on competition on the routes that it covers joint venture with virgin atlanticedit on december   delta announced that it would spend  million to acquire a  percent stake in virgin atlantic these shares were previously held by singapore airlines as a part of this agreement both airlines would share the costs and revenues from all of the joint venture flights the airlines operated the two airlines planned to operate a total of  roundtrip flights between the uk and north america including nine daily roundtrip flights between london heathrow and new york city airports john f kennedy international airport and newark liberty international airport the two airlines application for antitrust immunity was granted by the united states department of transportation on september   fleetedit delta air lines has the largest boeing  fleet of any airline main article delta air lines fleet as of january update delta operates a fleet of more than  aircraft manufactured by airbus boeing and mcdonnell douglas delta operates the largest boeing  boeing  boeing  mcdonnell douglas md and mcdonnell douglas md fleets in the world and the largest airbus a fleet of any us airline prior to its  merger with northwest airlines deltas fleet was made up of solely boeing and mcdonnell douglas aircraft airbus aircraft from northwest joined the fleet after the merger and more have since been added unlike other us legacy carriers delta often seeks to acquire and utilize older aircraft especially narrowbodies and they have created an extensive mro maintenance repair and overhaul organization called techops to support them the oldest aircraft in the fleet are the mcdonnell douglas mds with an average age of over  years however in early  delta began talks with airbus boeing and bombardier to discuss replacing the mcdonnell douglas dcs mds and older a and  aircraft on august   delta placed an order for  boeing er aircraft and deferred an order of  small narrowbody jets until  as part of its strategy to utilize less expensive used airplanes delta agreed in  to lease  boeing s acquired by southwest airlines during their acquisition of airtran airways they would be used as replacements for the dc fleet and some seat regional aircraft like the crj and  the first revenue flight was on october   delta officially retired its last dc on january   it was used on an asneeded basis until january   when the last one was removed from service delta was the final us carrier operating the dc as a continuation of the narrowbody fleet refresh and expansion delta ordered  bombardier cs aircraft and an additional  options on april   becoming the first americ