video entertainment the md introduced deltas first ife system with lcd monitors in  and the  introduced deltas first inseat video system in  initially using the rockwell collins total entertainment system deltas first alldigital ife system with avod panasonic efx was first introduced in  on deltas former lowcost subsidiary song the rockwell collins ife system on the s was replaced by the panasonic efx system in  followed by the panasonic ex in  the panasonic efx and ex systems are trademarked by delta as delta on demand in the spring of  delta installed the panasonic efx avod system in economy on six ers that are used on routes that are  hours or longer delta also announced it would be installing avod in economy class on all boeing er and  aircraft over the next  years on july   delta announced that it would be the launch customer of the new ex avod system with the eco i integrated smart monitor a new ultralightweight ife system by panasonic avionics corporation and zodiac seats us the systems have been installed on the entire  fleet as of october  and are currently being installed on the er fleet except for the six aircraft previously retrofitted with the efx system in  a different version of the integrated smart monitor developed by panasonic avionics corporation and be aerospace is currently being installed on the airbus a fleet these seats will also be installed on the boeing  and new boeing er fleet and will replace the existing seats and monitors on the international boeing  fleet in  delta began replacing the overhead crt monitors on the premerger delta  fleet with new lcd monitors this was completed in late  the er fleet initially featured lcds over the aisles but were replaced in  by the panasonic efx avod system when the last of the ers were converted from domestic to international use crt projectors were originally featured in economy class on boeing –s with the international ers also featuring ceilingmounted crt displays over the aisles which have since replaced by lcd monitors and are now in the process of being converted to the efx avod system when deltas extwa etops s were first delivered they featured a system made by sony transcom a former subsidiary of sony now sold to rockwell collins system that was factory installed for twa the system featured overhead dropdown lcd monitors similar to deltas nontranscon s and s delta replaced the sony transcom system with the panasonic efx system featuring inseat video and avod at the same time as the new businesselite seats and slimline economy class seats were installed current fleetedit audio and video are available on all aircraft except for the airbus a mcdonnell douglas md and md selected boeing  and delta connection aircraft boeing er lr and  aircraft along with those  and a aircraft that have completed cabin modifications feature the panasonic ex system compared to the older efx system this offers greater storage capacity as well as lighter and larger personal video screens boeing er aircraft selected  aircraft as well as the remaining internationally configured boeing er aircraft that have not completed cabin modifications use the panasonic efx avod system on these  aircraft avod is available only in the delta one class while the system includes overhead lcd monitors and audio programming for passengers seated in the economy cabin the unmodified airbus a aircraft feature the panasonic i avod system in all cabins this system includes supplemental lcd monitors over the aisles for displaying the safety video and moving map domestic boeing –s boeing –s as well as selected transcontinental boeing –s and selected boeing –s using the panasonic efx system also feature live television via dish network in both first class and economy some boeing s as well as all boeing –s feature systems with dropdown lcd displays below the overhead bins all aircraft with avod feature panasonics ixplor moving map program s with overhead video and the coach sections of er aircraft with overhead video feature the rockwell collins airshow moving map which is often shown during takeoff and landing other aircraft formerly equipped with the rockwell collins airshow moving map included the lockheed l and  mcdonnell douglas md and boeing er and er the l and md fleet have since been retired while the er and er have since had their airshow systems replaced by the panasonic ixplor system built into the efx and ex avod systems delta sky magazineedit delta sky magazine and its online edition are published by msp communications in minneapolis minnesota reward programsedit skymilesedit main article skymiles skymiles is the frequent flyer program for delta air lines sky clubsedit delta air lines airport lounges are called sky clubs membership options include single visit passes and annual memberships that can be purchased with either money or miles international business class passengers get free access membership can also be granted through top level delta status or with the purchase of some american express credit cards features vary by location but generally include free drinks including alcoholic beverages snacks and reading material wifi is free for members and guests and is mostly provided in the usa by att other benefits for sky club members include reciprocal lounge access with other skyteam members and deltas other partners originally deltas membershipbased airport clubs were called crown room lounges with northwests called worldclubs skybonusedit on november   delta air lines launched skybonusnot in citation given a program aimed toward smalltomedium businesses spending between  and  annually on air travel businesses can earn points toward free travel and upgrades as well as sky club memberships and skymiles silver medallion status points are earned on paid travel based on a variety of fare amount paid booking code and place origin or destination while enrolled businesses are able to earn points toward free travel the travelling passenger is still eligible to earn skymiles during his or her travel in early  delta air lines merged its skybonus program with northwests similar biz perks program environmental initiativesedit in  delta air lines was given an award from the united states environmental protection agencys design for the environment dfe program for their use of prekote a more environmentally friendly nonhexavalent chromium surface pretreatment on its aircraft replacing hazardous chemicals formerly used to improve paint adhesion and prevent corrosion in addition prekote reduces water usage by twothirds and reduces wastewater treatment prekote is also saving money by reducing the time needed to paint each airplane with time savings of eight to ten percent it will save an estimated more than  million annually sponsorshipsedit boeing er painted in pink livery for breast cancer research foundation bcrf at munich airport in  delta served as the official airline of the  summer olympics in atlanta the  winter olympics held in salt lake city and is also the official airline for major league baseball teams such as the atlanta braves cincinnati reds detroit tigers minnesota twins new york mets new york yankees san diego padres st louis cardinals and the washington nationals delta also carries the buffalo sabres los angeles kings los angeles lakers los angeles sparks chelsea fc madison square garden seattle seahawks seattle sounders fc copa américa centenario atlanta dream atlanta falcons atlanta hawks atlanta united fc and the cleveland cavaliers delta awards the annual delta prize for global understanding in conjunction with the university of georgia vivint smart home arena in salt lake city home of the nbas utah jazz was originally known as the delta center delta held the naming rights to the arena from  to  and continues to be an official sponsor of the team delta was a sponsor of the  north american international auto show in detroit delta is the official airline for the grammy awards also in  delta is the official airline for the durham bulls minor league baseball team in august  delta continued its push into new york city by securing its first arts sponsorship the deal with the whitney museum makes delta the official and exclusive airline of the museum delta has sponsored various lgbt pride events in atlanta new york city salt lake city and detroit delta also sponsors the university of georgia and georgia tech athletics and provides transportation for away games delta air lines is the official airline of syracuse university athletics and has marketing relationships with eight additional ncaa athletic programs—boston college brigham young duke georgia tech university of georgia university of michigan university of minnesota and university of north carolina delta serves as the charter carrier for  ncaa football programs in  delta sponsored yomiuri giants a nippon professional baseball team this is the first time that delta sponsored a foreign sports team in popular cultureedit deltalinaedit main article deltalina as part of the rebranding project a safety video featuring a flight attendant showed up on youtube in early  getting over  million views and the attention of news outlets specifically for the videos tone mixed with the serious safety message the flight attendant katherine lee was dubbed deltalina by a member of flyertalk for her resemblance to angelina jolie delta had considered several styles for its current safety video including animation before opting for a video presenting a flight attendant speaking to the audience the video was filmed on a boeing  accidents and incidentsedit the following are major accidents and incidents that occurred on delta mainline aircraft for northwest airlines incidents see northwest airlines accidents and incidents for delta connection incidents see delta connection incidents and accidents delta air lines reported incidents flight date aircraft location description casualties fatal serious minor uninjured ground na april   dc columbus georgia a vultee bt owned by the tuskegee aviation institute landed on top of a dc which was flying from macon to columbus       march   dc chicago midway airport crashed near chicago municipal midway airport shortly after takeoff while en route to miami officials determined that longitudinal control of the airplane was lost resulting in the crash the cause for the loss of control remains undetermined       may   dc marshall texas crashed  miles  km east of marshall texas the flight which originated from dallas love field was on approach to shreveport louisiana the crash was attributed to adverse weather conditions with a thunderstorm in the area       may   convair  hartsfield–jackson atlanta international airport crashed during a training exercise in atlanta the aircraft stalled and crashed killing all four crew members       march   dc louis armstrong new orleans international airport crashed during a training exercise near new orleans international airport the improper use of flight and power controls by both instructor and the captaintrainee during a simulated twoengine out landing approach resulted in the loss of control the aircraft crashed into a residential area destroying several homes and a motel complex and killing  people on the ground       may   dc greater southwest international airport crashed during landing procedures in fort worth texas the probable cause of the accident was wake turbulence resulting from a touchandgo landing moments before of american airlines flight  operated using a dc the right wing hit the ground causing a fire resulting in the aircraft being written off       december   convair  ohare international airport the delta cv taxied across runway l in heavy fog at the same time north central airlines flight  a dc took off from the same runway the aircraft collided    severity unknown    july   dc boston logan international airport crashed into a seawall contributing to the accident was a defective flight deck instrument giving the crew misleading guidance during the instrument approach in visibility less than a half mile with foot  m cloud ceilings  occupants died including leopold chouinard who died from burns months after the accident leaving no survivors       november   dc chattanooga metropolitan airport crashed into approach lights during a thunderstorm       august   lockheed l dallas–fort worth international airport on a fort lauderdale–dallasfort worth los angeles route the plane crashed due to severe microburstinduced wind shear one person on the ground was killed as the plane crossed a highway the crash would later become the subject of a television movie numerous changes to pilot wind shear training weather forecasting and wind shear detection were made as a result of this crash       july   lockheed l north atlantic ocean near collision with a continental  carrying  passengers and crew both the delta londoncincinnati and continental londonnewark were heading to the us with nearly  people total on both aircraft the delta flight strayed  miles  km off course to the south from its assigned c track during its flight and came within  feet  m of colliding with the  as the l flew under it in canadian airspace flying on the d track there are five westbound and five eastbound tracks from the united states to the united kingdom had the planes actually collided it could have tied the tenerife airport disaster as the deadliest aviation accident in history    all   august   boeing  dallas–fort worth international airport crashed after takeoff bound for salt lake city utah the investigation stated the probable cause of this accident to be improper configuration of the flaps and leading edge slats       july   md pensacola international airport an uncontained engine failure of the port left engine on the aircraft resulted in a fan hub piercing the cabin the flight was scheduled to fly to atlanta the aircraft involved in this accident nda was repaired as of february  the faa reports the aircraft involved in the incident is still in service        september   boeing – en route from boston logan international airport flight  bound for los angeles international airport was caught in the path of united airlines flight  the two aircraft were so close that atc were initially confused as to which plane had been hijacked the delta pilot managed to avoid united  and the flight was later diverted to cleveland hopkins international airport    all    february   mcdonnell douglas md dublin airport flight  from atlanta skidded off the runway at dublin airport in high winds the port engine of md nde had severe damage    all   march   mcdonnell douglas md laguardia airport while landing in heavy snowfall flight  from atlanta departed the left side of runway while traveling approximately  miles per hour  kmh coming to rest nearly perpendicular to the runway with its nose on an embankment beside the waters of flushing bay the accident resulted in damage to the aircrafts left wing including a fuel leak nose landing gear well main electronics bay nose radomeweather radar and undercarriage damage forward of the front doors the aircrafts braking system and condition of the runway surface are being considered as possible causes of the incident       june   boeing  over chinese airspace flight  from detroit metropolitan wayne county airport to seoul incheon international airport was over chinese airspace when the aircraft flew through a severe hailstorm this resulted in substantial damage to the aircrafts radome hail penetrating nose causing a large hole as well as leading edges of the wing destroyed and damage to the tail plane this aircraft was written off due to its age and because delta had already began retiring its boeing  fleet temporary repairs were made to make it airworthy and the aircraft was ferried from seoul to pinal airpark in marana arizona    all   august   airbus a en route from boston logan airport to salt lake city the plane had to make an emergency landing at the denver international airport after a hailstorm at the nebraskacolorado border about  nm east of denver severely damaged its windshields and nose cone impairing visibility through the windshields and disabling the weather radar engines were also damaged and the hail also partially tore the planes fuselage        july   boeing  over canadian airspace flight  from seattle to beijing had an altercation midflight where a male passenger named joseph daniel hudek attempted to open an emergency exit which is impossible at that altitude due to the difference in air pressure and assaulted a flight attendant in the firstclass cabin several other passengers became involved in the situation in an attempt to subdue hudek the flight returned to seattle without further incident where hudek was arrested the flight attendant and one other passenger who tried to subdue the suspect were taken to the hospital for nonlifethreatening injuries federal charges were filed against hudek and he may face up to  years in prison and fines up to us      the attempted bombing of northwest airlines flight  on december   occurred four days before the operating certificates of northwest and delta were combined december   the aircraft involved in the incident was in delta livery and reported in some early news reports as delta flight  hijackingsedit there have been over a dozen attempted hijackings that resulted in no injuries and the surrender of the often lone hijacker these incidents are not included the following are notable hijackings because of fatalities or success in forcing the aircraft to fly to another country in  a delta dc was hijacked to havana cuba this was the first successful hijacking to cuba from the us since citation needed and was the start of multiple hijacking attempts to cuba in the late s this coincided with the introduction of passenger screening using metal detectors in us airports starting in the late s additional hijackings that resulted in no injuries and the flight landing in cuba include march   delta  new orleansdallas  august   delta  miamitampa  july   delta  miamitampa  june   delta  new york laguardiafort lauderdale l july   a delta flight  a detroit to miami dc flight was hijacked to algiers algeria by  hijackers the aircraft stopped in boston to pick up an international navigator the flight was allowed to return with passengers to the us stopping in barcelona for refueling on february   samuel byck an unemployed tire salesman from pennsylvania stormed aboard delta air lines flight  dc flight at baltimore friendship airport now baltimorewashington international thurgood marshall airport scheduled to fly to atlanta and shot both pilots killing the first officer fred jones he intended to crash the plane into the white house after shooting the pilots the hijacker grabbed a passenger and demanded that she fly the aircraft the hijacking attempt ended when after a standoff with police byck was shot twice through an aircraft porthole by a md policeman severely wounding him before police stormed the plane byck killed himself the plane never left the gate during this incident on august   a delta air lines l on a san juan to los angeles flight was hijacked and flown to cuba the hijacker was jailed by cuban authorities and all passengers were released unharmed on september   a delta air lines new orleans to atlanta flight was taken over by two hijackers and forced to fly to cuba the flight continued to atlanta after stopping in havana the hijackers were imprisoned by cuban authorities one hijacker was released and later sought us residency the suspect was later arrested by us authorities in  and sentenced to  years in prison the following year see alsoedit book delta air lines atlanta portal companies portal aviation portal air transportation in the united states delta flight museum list of airlines of the united states list of airports in the united states list of companies of the united states transportation in the united states r